pageContext.claim: “We have all sorts of co-op plans and other plans. And people are going to them by the millions. And it's been an honor.”
pageContext.analysis: The co-op plans in Obamacare essentially went out of business. Trump appears to be referring to association plans. But when the rules for the plans were released over the summer, trade associations that had been expected to embrace them said they were not workable as the rules were too complex. The plans will be rolled out in the fall, and it's unclear how many have been sold, but there is no way it could already be in the millions. The plans don’t have to cover the full menu of 10 “essential” kinds of benefits required by the Affordable Care Act.
